4. The goto statement is used to jump to a label named "i".
5. The variable f_d is assigned a value of 6L.
6. The function fn1 is called recursively.
7. The return statement returns the value 0xEEACFBBFL.
8. The label "i" is defined, which is the target of the goto statement.
9. The function fn1 is called again.
10. The second return statement returns the value 0xEEACFBBFL.
11. The main function is defined, which returns an int data type.

Based on this analysis, the only redundant data type identified is the char data type used for the return type of the fn1 function.
